gumland
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:area of poor soil, once supporting kauri forests and containing kauri gum (often pl). Also  (rarely) kauri-gum(-)land.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Probably ellipt. for kauri-gum-land, poor quality land, formerly (?originally) under kauri forest, hence where  kauri gum has been, or may be, found.  ?Sg as a descriptive term - contrast gumlands  (see also gum country).
